CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "Congratulations! Robert E. (Pappy) Williams, left: Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald, right, and Mrs. Mary Ellen Hodge, center, exchange congratulations after the Fifth Ward election Tuesday night at A. Leo Weil School. Mr. Williams was re-elected chairman;  Mrs. Hodge became the new vice chairman, and Alderman Fitzgerald was the choice for secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robert E. "Pappy" Williams, Mary Ellen Hodge, and Harry B. Fitzgerald clasping hands in auditorium of A. Leo Weil School
